properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 2 at 4:05PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the High Wind Warning, northwest to north winds 30
to 45 mph with damaging gusts to 70 mph. Isolated gusts to 80
mph possible in the foothills of the Santa Ynez range. For the
Freeze Watches, sub- freezing temperatures as low as 30
degrees will be possible.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County South Coast.

* WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, until noon PST Monday. For
the first Freeze Watch, from late Monday night through Tuesday
morning. For the second Freeze Watch, from late Tuesday night
through Wednesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. High profile
vehicles, including big rigs could be blown over by the
powerful winds. Frost and freeze conditions could kill crops,
and other sensitive vegetation.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds tonight across the Santa
Ynez range and Santa Barbara south coast. Major roadways that
could be impacted by the powerful winds and wind damage
include Highways 101, 154, and 192.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Avoid travel
if possible during the height of the windstorm, and remember to
check the latest road reports if you must travel.

Take steps now to protect tender plants from the cold. Plan for
extra time to defrost vehicle windshields.
